ANTHRAX - ALBANIA: (DIBER) BOVINE
*********************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Mon 9 Jul 2018, 6:42 PM
Source: Dita [in Albanian, machine trans., edited]
http://www.gazetadita.al/semundja-e-rrezikshme-e-gjedheve-alarmon-banoret-e-matit/


The Nodular Dermatosis [outbreak of Lumpy Skin disease] has not yet passed, and Mat shows another cattle disease. It is about Anthrax, for which the 1st case was noted.

According to "Balkanweb", the case was recorded in the village Frankth of the Komsi Administrative Unit in the Municipality of Mat. Immediately after that, residents urgently sought the vaccination of their cattle.

Meanwhile, the veterinarian of the Veterinary Service at the Agriculture Office Mat, Selman Kurti, said that this case was confirmed by the Veterinary Institute. He added that this disease is caught by humans by consuming meat [of affected animals].

--
