******
[2]
Date: Mon 9 Jul 2018
Source: SYRI [in Albanian, trans. Corr.SZ, edited]
https://www.syri.net/sociale/176971/alarm-ne-mat-shenohet-nje-rast-me-antraks-tek-bagetite/


Recently, residents of the area faced Dermatosis Nodular [Lumpy Skin] disease, which caused major damage to the area's farmers. After this disease disappeared, the farmers were compensated by the government with imported cows.

But an outbreak of acute disease has again appeared and has caused the 1st death, namely to compensatory cattle given to the farmers who had been affected by Nodular Dermatosis.

The case was recorded in the village of Frankth of the Komsi Administrative Unit in the Municipality of Mat. Residents insist that the state vaccinate the other cattle.

Meanwhile, the veterinarian of the Veterinary Service at the Agriculture Office Mat, Selman Kurti, said the case was confirmed by the Veterinary High Institute. Kurti said the disease is also contagious to humans in 2 forms, affecting the infected bovine and consuming his flesh. Starting from this he appealed to farmers to instantly notify instances if they have unexpected bouts of cattle.

Because this disease has affected an imported animal, specialists associate this with their weak immunity in the country.

--
